column1:
I flunked three of my finals in one day, too.
I was really freakin' out.

I had so many makeup lectures in a row,
I almost wasn't able to come over today...
Heheh, then I win! I only flunked ONE final!

You two are the same as always. Can't you at
least take your classes a bit more seriously?

Watch out, Miss President's gonna unleash her
fist of justice!

Geez... Will you please forget about that
already?
So, is college life all it's cracked up to be?

Yes, it's going well. I've been using the time to
take care of the core curriculum.

I've been busy too, but it's also a lot of fun.
For example, I've learned how to selectively
breed certain vegetables.

Wait—aren't you in the management program,
though?

Yes, but students are allowed to take courses
beyond their own programs if they feel so
inclined.

They even offer agricultural science courses.
You can learn all sorts of neat things, like the
correlation between soil nutrients and yield...
Guh. That'd put me to sleep in a minute flat...
And you, Futaba? How's school been for you?

At this point, the only hellish parts are the
commute and P.E.!

Uh-huh, uh-huh! Praise me more, keep it
comin'!

Well, how 'bout you, then? You're the one
we're the most curious about. You doin' okay
back home?

Well, that's a relief—even though you seem like
you'd be fine no matter where you ended up.

*giggle* Your personality hasn't changed at all,
either.
Well, I've been gettin' by too, but...

Without you around, it's sorta like stuff is just
kinda... bleh.
Of course! He's our leader; it's only natural!

Heheh! Once a phantom thief, always a
phantom thief!

Well, what say we start coming up with summer
vacation plans? Anyone have any ideas?
Ooh, right! We should figure that stuff out!

You're fine to stay here through all of vacation,
right?

How 'bout a trip, guys? C'mon, we've got
a whole month to rage!

Um, aren't you forgetting about your
homework?

Not only do you have homework, but you're
third-years now. You need to start thinking not
just about graduation, but post-graduation—

Ah! No, stop! Don't bring that up, not now,
please!

Back to the topic at hand—if I may suggest
Kyoto. I'll find an abundance of inspiration
if we tour each temple and shrine.

Oh, the sheer wealth of beauty I can witness
in a whole month! I can hear the treasures
of our history calling to me!

Yeah, if it's a month-long art tour, I'm totally
gonna pass.

A trip does sound nice, but what if we all went
camping first?

We can all go hiking and stuff during the day,
and even throw together a barbecue at night!

B-B-Barbecue!? Aren't those always b-big
gatherings for people who socialize IRL?

*giggle* Sounds fun. You can leave the
firewood-chopping to me.

Kickin' summer off right with a barbecue buffet!
Sounds badass to me—how 'bout you?

Look for decent marbling in the cuts! That's
how you get the real good stuff. Trust me on
this.

Hmm, good point. A proper meal needs a bit
of color to it.

It does sound rather fitting for the summer.
I like the idea, but we'll need an awful lot of
vegetables to balance it out.

Ha... A barbecue is one of the few things in this
world that could pull me away from art. Our
history's treasures can wait a bit longer.

Choosing food over art? You sure your priorities
are solid there, Inari?

All right, our first reunion party has been
unanimously decided: we're going camping!

I have compiled a list of items recommended
for camping.

There is a sporting and travel goods store near
705 in Shibuya. Customer reviews rate this as
the best relevant store in your area.

The virtual assistant, EMMA. You haven't
heard of it yet?

Oh, I think I have. It knows, like, basically
everything and does all sorts of stuff for you,
right?

Aw, yeah, it's got this eye that thinks for it,
right?
I think you mean "AI," not "an eye."

It can search all kinds of databases, conduct
navigation, manage your schedule, even talk
out logic problems and stuff with you...

The makers go on about how you can ask it
anything and you'll get the best possible
answer.

I remember seeing a demo of one on TV the
other day. They were showing off its functions
and talking about how it's the next big thing.

Yep, that's it all right. Pretty solid tech,
considering they're roughly a thousand
times smarter than Ryuji.

It does sound kinda cool, though. I bet it'd
tell us where all the best ramen shops are.

Yeah, you should all download it! I'm tellin' ya,
it's the bees' knees.

I suppose it'd at least be handy if we ran into
any trouble while camping.
That's a good idea. Why don't you get it too?
Hello, this is EMMA. I am pleased to meet you.
Again, I am EMMA, your helpful virtual assistant.
Looks like you've got it figured out.

I sent you all friend requests—please don't blow
them off!

"Displaying recommended camping items..."
So, EMMA came up with all that?

Impressive, no? And it's not just random junk
for sale, either!

It takes into account the season, the weather,
your personal profile, and even your location
for all its recommendations.
For real? Damn, that thing's eye's crazy!

Well, should we split up and buy everything
EMMA's listed for us?

Aw, can't we do it tomorrow? It's so hot out...
I bet [1B]S1's beat from the travelin', too.

We just went through all the effort to meet up
at the hideout, yeah? So let's make the most
of it!

Indeed, I have an absolute plethora of
discussion topics for us to mull over.

Particularly, matters such as modern art and
the possibilities within it in our current age...

We had a great time
catching up together...
